          </div>
          <div class="content">
              <p>I had finally finished my Udemy course. My final project was called Yelp Camp. In order to follow along we all used the same design to get started and campgrounds was the theme. The site will be redesigned into something more useful down the road but for now it taught me about databases, node, authentication and so much more.  Yelp Camp can be seen here <a href=” https://boiling-lake-05560.herokuapp.com/”>Yelp Camp</a> .</p>
              
              <p>After I was done with the Udemy course I was excited to move on and create websites and apps. I did find myself as I said in the last blog a little lost at times because I had stuffed an entire course into such a short time period. I had all of the knowledge in my brain but remembering it all without looking things up was the issue. I felt pretty down sometime when I would Google something stupid that I felt I should know.</p>
              <p>The week or so after completing the Udemy course was the toughest for me, that feeling of what now was really hitting me hard. I knew I needed to practice what I had learned. </p>
              <p>During my Udemy course I was given an excellent opportunity by <a href="https://zerotomastery.io/">Zero to Mastery</a>. They had been offering up 6 months of free online classes to people who had been affected by Covid-19. I filled out their online form and told them I was out of work and looking to move out of the restaurant industry. I was lucky enough to be offered 6 months of free classes.</p>
              <p>I decided I would do ZTM’s 2020 Web Developers Course. I know why would I choose that? My thought process was I would go through the course fast and complete the assignments without coding along. In my mind this was just the challenge and also the opportunity to get some added skills as this course also offered React.</p>
              <p>I flew though HTML and CSS, crushed the quizzes and moved onto JavaScript on my second day in the course… but then my eyes were opened. </p>
